<body>
<header id="title-block-header">
<h1 class="title">Shorthelp</h1>
</header>
<h2 id="aottext-short-help">Aottext Short-help</h2>
<h4 id="hide-the-aottext-window">Hide the Aottext window</h4>
<p>Autotext is always on top, but sometimes this behavior is unwanted
temporarily.<br />
To hide the Aottext-window use one of the 4 actions:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr class="header">
<th>No.</th>
<th>hide with key</th>
<th>show with key</th>
<th>remarks</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr class="odd">
<td>1</td>
<td>[Left-shift] + [Right-mousebutton]</td>
<td>same again</td>
<td>#1 and #2 can be mixed</td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>2</td>
<td>[Left-shift] + [Control] + &quot;mouse-over&quot;</td>
<td>Mouse-over minimized Edit-field</td>
<td>#1 and #2 can be mixed</td>
</tr>
<tr class="odd">
<td>3</td>
<td>[Alt] + [a]</td>
<td>same again</td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr class="even">
<td>4</td>
<td>H30 button</td>
<td>[Alt] + [a] twice</td>
<td>timeout: 30 seconds</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>Enabled by [Config-file] -&gt; [user] -&gt; quickHideEnabled=1<br />
Or just close the app (content is auto-saved) and reopen it later.</p>
<h4 id="content-autosave">Content autosave</h4>
<p>Content is saved if it was changed and:</p>
<ul>
<li>on any &quot;hide&quot;-operation,</li>
<li>on exiting the app.</li>
<li>by pressing the &quot;Save&quot; button, the content is always saved,
regardless of whether it has been changed.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="file-history">File history</h4>
<p>Use [Alt] + [Mousewheel] to cycle thru the history.</p>
<h4 id="vmode-button">VMode-button</h4>
<p>VMode moves the Aottext-window to the right side and increases the
vertical size.<br />
Gives a better overview if you want to copy multible lines of text.</p>
<h4 id="hide-and-exit">HIDE and EXIT</h4>
<p>Are context sensitiv buttons.<br />
If menu [Setup] -&gt; [Edit Config] is selected, the functionallity is
chanced to &quot;SAVE&quot; &quot;CANCEL&quot;.</p>
</body>
